AGI - The State Police and the Penitentiary Police are engaged in an operation, coordinated by the prosecutor of Avellino, for the execution of an application order of precautionary measure, issued by the Irpino gip, against 11 investigated for attempted aggravated murder. The victim of the group was a prisoner in the Circus House of Avellino, and the attempt to kill him was consumed in a revolt of the same prisoners, with the contrast between two distinct criminal groups within the penitentiary Irpino.&nbsp;
The precautionary measures mark the closure of the investigations that the prosecutor has entrusted to the Mobile Team of Avellino and the Nic of the Penitentiary Police to identify the responsible for the brutal aggression occurred on the evening of 22 October in the prison of Bellizzi Irpino: a punitive raid perpetrated against a 25-year-old Neapolitan prisoner, Paolo Piccolo, in cell 8 of the Common Section reduced in severe conditions and hospitalized in Moscow.
A group of detainees managed to enter the first floor in the right area of the penitentiary, despite the intervention of the Penitentiary agents reached cell number 8 where Piccolo was found who was plagued. The 11 recipients of the measure had already seen delivery of a guarantee information of the Luigi Iglio pm and a notification of the seizure of the material found during searchs carried out a few hours after the raid: shoes, suits, neck warmer on which technical checks were made.&nbsp;

